<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/165.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-04-27"><hi rend="italic">April 27,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Leishman requests that instructions be sent to cruisers at Gibraltar
                            to go direct to Mersine and Alexandretta, leaving embassy free, if
                            necessary, to send them to other points.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>